      "snippet": "  #168 Description Issue body actions Problem Currently, the BaseReader class accepts a adapter parameter that is used to transform input data into the required document format. However, if a custom adapter function is used, it does not have access to the BaseReader instance variables, limiting its flexibility and requiring workarounds. Suggested Enhancement I propose modifying the assignment of the adapter to use MethodType from the types module. This change will allow the custom adapter to access instance variables and methods, greatly increasing its utility and aligning with common Python practices for class method customization. Example Use Case Consider a scenario where the adapter needs to access text_key and id_key from the reader instance to properly format the input data. With the proposed change, this becomes straightforward and the code remains clean and maintainable. This change would make the BaseReader more versatile and user-friendly for complex data loading scenarios. I",
